01:17:17,194 --> 01:17:19,333
<i>I even pack extra fortune cookies for him!</i>

1753
01:17:19,530 --> 01:17:21,601
<i>Excuse me, what's Chinese for mental case?</i>

1754
01:17:22,900 --> 01:17:24,038
<i>Hello?</i>

1755
01:17:30,741 --> 01:17:32,721
<i>We were cruising
and heard the alarm. ls everyone okay?</i>

1756
01:17:32,910 --> 01:17:33,650
<i>Yes.</i>

1757
01:17:33,844 --> 01:17:36,552
<i>No, he's dead! The car killed him!</i>

1758
01:17:36,747 --> 01:17:38,624
<i>He came out of nowhere!</i>

1759
01:17:38,816 --> 01:17:40,489
<i>Officer, you're wasting your time.</i>

1760
01:17:40,685 --> 01:17:42,187
<i>What happened? Why are the police here?</i>

1761
01:17:42,386 --> 01:17:43,694
<i>Why is the alarm on?</i>

1762
01:17:43,888 --> 01:17:45,128
<i>- Oh, hi!
- Mommy!</i>

1763
01:17:45,322 --> 01:17:46,596
<i>- Was there a break-in?
- It's nothing.</i>

1764
01:17:46,791 --> 01:17:49,829
<i>It's absolutely nothing.
What are you doing home?</i>

1765
01:17:50,027 --> 01:17:51,165
<i>I killed Carl!</i>

1766
01:17:51,362 --> 01:17:53,137
<i>- What?
- You killed Carl? How?</i>

1767
01:17:53,330 --> 01:17:55,503
<i>Who is Carl? Is he a family member?</i>

1768
01:17:55,700 --> 01:17:56,542
<i>- Yes!
- No!</i>

1769
01:17:56,734 --> 01:17:58,372
<i>He's a kangaroo!</i>

1770
01:17:58,569 --> 01:17:59,479
<i>He's a what?</i>

1771
01:17:59,670 --> 01:18:00,808
<i>Turner, your eye!</i>

1772
01:18:01,005 --> 01:18:02,177
<i>How did that happen?</i>

1773
01:18:02,840 --> 01:18:03,818
<i>Artie did it?</i>

1774
01:18:04,041 --> 01:18:07,545
<i>Oh, no, no, no. lvan's sister did it. I did that.</i>

1775
01:18:07,745 --> 01:18:08,723
<i>You hit Mom?</i>

1776
01:18:08,813 --> 01:18:09,848
<i>It was an accident!</i>

1777
01:18:10,047 --> 01:18:11,287
<i>Ma'am, would you like to file a complaint?</i>

1778
01:18:11,482 --> 01:18:12,483
<i>No!</i>

1779
01:18:12,583 --> 01:18:13,653
<i>We were playing a game.</i>

1780
01:18:13,751 --> 01:18:15,230
<i>That's the dress.</i>

1781
01:18:15,419 --> 01:18:16,659
<i>Does she have make-up on?</i>

1782
01:18:17,922 --> 01:18:19,162
<i>Don't growl at us.</i>

1783
01:18:19,356 --> 01:18:20,164
<i>This is unbelievable.</i>

1784
01:18:20,357 --> 01:18:22,530
<i>We leave and she's 12,
we come home and she's 16.</i>

1785
01:18:22,893 --> 01:18:23,871
<i>Boys, go in the house.</i>

1786
01:18:24,061 --> 01:18:25,631
<i>Turner, turn off the alarm, please.</i>

1787
01:18:25,830 --> 01:18:27,537
<i>You know, you're not supposed
to be back until tomorrow.</i>

1788
01:18:27,732 --> 01:18:29,473
<i>Well, we were just so curious...</i>

1789
01:18:29,667 --> 01:18:32,671
<i>as to why Barker was nearly
killed this morning at the X Games!</i>

1790
01:18:32,870 --> 01:18:34,474
<i>Uh-oh! Get your taser ready.</i>

1791
01:18:35,372 --> 01:18:36,350
<i>That's not right.</i>

1792
01:18:36,540 --> 01:18:38,645
<i>Barker was at a play date
this morning with Artie.</i>

1793
01:18:38,843 --> 01:18:39,753
<i>Oh. yeah?</i>

1794
01:18:43,447 --> 01:18:45,484
<i>I was in a little bind...</i>

1795
01:18:45,683 --> 01:18:47,993
<i>and I had to take him
with me on some business.</i>

1796
01:18:48,185 --> 01:18:49,926
<i>What business did you have
at the X Games?</i>

1797
01:18:50,121 --> 01:18:52,101
<i>Yeah, Artie, what business?</i>

1798
01:18:57,228 --> 01:18:58,366
<i>Um...</i>

1799
01:18:59,563 --> 01:19:01,600
<i>Aren't we forgetting
the most serious issue here?</i>

1800
01:19:01,799 --> 01:19:02,834
<i>What issue?</i>

1801
01:19:02,933 --> 01:19:05,209
<i>The death of an imaginary kangaroo.</i>

1802
01:19:05,402 --> 01:19:06,403
<i>He's imaginary?</i>

1803
01:19:06,604 --> 01:19:07,582
<i>Yes!</i>

1804
01:19:09,774 --> 01:19:10,752
<i>You can go.</i>

1805
01:19:15,713 --> 01:19:18,216
<i>Would someone please explain
what happened to Carl?</i>

1806
01:19:18,415 --> 01:19:19,621
<i>We were playing Kick the Can...</i>

1807
01:19:19,817 --> 01:19:22,093
<i>and it started to rain,
so we all came indoors...</i>

1808
01:19:22,286 --> 01:19:24,789
<i>and I was helping
Harper get dressed for her party.</i>

1809
01:19:24,989 --> 01:19:26,935
<i>A party? You're throwing a party?</i>

1810
01:19:27,124 --> 01:19:27,924
<i>No, Dad, I'm going to a party.</i>

1811
01:19:27,925 --> 01:19:28,528
<i>No, Dad, I'm going to a party.</i>

1812
01:19:28,726 --> 01:19:29,704
<i>For a boy who likes her.</i>

1813
01:19:29,894 --> 01:19:31,532
<i>A boy? What boy?</i>

1814
01:19:31,729 --> 01:19:34,141
<i>The night before your audition?
Are you kidding?</i>

1815
01:19:34,331 --> 01:19:35,469
<i>I told her she could go.</i>

1816
01:19:35,666 --> 01:19:38,647
<i>It's ridiculous. It is out of the question.</i>

1817
01:19:38,836 --> 01:19:40,713
<i>Maybe it's ridiculous for me to spend</i>

1818
01:19:40,805 --> 01:19:42,648
<i>all my time practicing the violin...</i>

1819
01:19:42,840 --> 01:19:46,310
<i>never doing anything else
and auditioning for a school tomorrow...</i>

1820
01:19:46,510 --> 01:19:48,490
<i>where I'm never going to do anything else</i>

1821
01:19:48,579 --> 01:19:50,490
<i>the whole rest of my life.</i>

1822
01:19:52,750 --> 01:19:53,785
<i>Huh?</i>

1823
01:19:55,152 --> 01:19:56,927
<i>Well, she's using her words.</i>

1824
01:19:57,121 --> 01:20:00,330
<i>Harper. Harper!
I cannot allow you to take a talent...</i>

1825
01:20:00,524 --> 01:20:03,733
<i>a gift to which you have
dedicated so much time and effort...</i>

1826
01:20:03,928 --> 01:20:06,238
<i>and throw it away on a whim.</i>

1827
01:20:06,430 --> 01:20:09,434
<i>I hate you and I wish
anyone else was my mother!</i>

1828
01:20:11,001 --> 01:20:12,947
<i>Maybe not those words.</i>

1829
01:20:13,337 --> 01:20:14,509
<i>Thanks, Mom and Dad.</i>

1830
01:20:14,705 --> 01:20:16,514
<i>I couldn't have
gotten through the week without you.</i>

1831
01:20:23,113 --> 01:20:24,683
<i>I say we head for the airport right now.</i>

1832
01:20:24,882 --> 01:20:27,488
<i>Don't even take our clothes
we just skedaddle.</i>

1833
01:20:31,355 --> 01:20:34,359
<i>I followed you for 35 years, Artie.</i>

1834
01:20:37,328 --> 01:20:41,708
<i>Wherever you needed to be,
that's where I was.</i>

1835
01:20:42,566 --> 01:20:44,603
<i>No complaints.</i>

1836
01:20:46,370 --> 01:20:48,646
<i>Well, some.</i>

1837
01:20:51,008 --> 01:20:52,851
<i>But this week...</i>

1838
01:20:53,978 --> 01:20:57,152
<i>This week was supposed to be about
us and our grandchildren.</i>

1839
01:20:58,182 --> 01:21:00,128
<i>Not you.</i>

1840
01:21:01,819 --> 01:21:03,355
<i>Not you.</i>

1841
01:21:06,957 --> 01:21:10,166
<i>Did you have to go to that audition?</i>

1842
01:21:11,929 --> 01:21:14,671
<i>It's not one of my better moments.</i>

1843
01:21:18,102 --> 01:21:20,605
<i>For one wonderful hour...</i>

1844
01:21:22,039 --> 01:21:26,852
<i>we weren't the "other" grandparents.</i>

1845
01:21:29,780 --> 01:21:30,850
<i>Oh.</i>

1846
01:21:30,948 --> 01:21:32,427
<i>There you are.</i>

1847
01:21:33,584 --> 01:21:35,222
<i>You okay?</i>

1848
01:21:36,820 --> 01:21:39,426
<i>I've had better Mommy days.</i>

1849
01:21:40,257 --> 01:21:44,103
<i>You know, it may not have been
horrible to let her go to that party.</i>

1850
01:21:44,295 --> 01:21:45,706
<i>I know.</i>

1851
01:21:45,896 --> 01:21:48,934
<i>I just walked into that scene and I freaked.</i>

1852
01:21:51,335 --> 01:21:53,144
<i>I can't believe my parents killed Carl.</i>

1853
01:21:53,671 --> 01:21:56,117
<i>Well, I was thinking about that.</i>

1854
01:21:56,307 --> 01:22:00,551
<i>You know, they didn't kill
Carl, only Barker could do that.</i>

1855
01:22:02,012 --> 01:22:06,757
<i>And it somehow took us
not being here for him to do it.</i>

1856
01:22:08,352 --> 01:22:10,593
<i>So, what's your point?</i>

1857
01:22:11,822 --> 01:22:14,132
<i>Maybe we coddle him too much.</i>

1858
01:22:15,092 --> 01:22:17,800
<i>Maybe he needed a little tough love...</i>

1859
01:22:17,995 --> 01:22:20,066
<i>to let go of his imaginary friend.</i>

1860
01:22:20,264 --> 01:22:24,906
<i>But, Phil, that would make my father right.</i>

1861
01:22:25,369 --> 01:22:27,940
<i>Yeah. We can't have any of that.</i>

1862
01:22:30,941 --> 01:22:31,783
<i>Harper?</i>

1863
01:22:35,546 --> 01:22:36,752
<i>I could come back.</i>

1864
01:22:36,947 --> 01:22:39,086
<i>No, no, no, it's okay.</i>

1865
01:22:39,283 --> 01:22:41,263
<i>I'm going to check on Barker.</i>

1866
01:22:43,787 --> 01:22:45,460
<i>Thanks, Phil.</i>

1867
01:22:53,630 --> 01:22:54,608
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

1868
01:22:58,202 --> 01:22:59,340
<i>For what?</i>

1869
01:22:59,536 --> 01:23:01,106
<i>Narrow it down for me, Dad.</i>

1870
01:23:01,305 --> 01:23:02,682
<i>For this week.</i>

1871
01:23:04,308 --> 01:23:06,219
<i>For almost getting Barker hurt today.</i>

1872
01:23:06,310 --> 01:23:08,153
<i>I just feel terrible about that.</i>

1873
01:23:10,214 --> 01:23:12,023
<i>What were you even doing there?</i>

1874
01:23:18,022 --> 01:23:20,730
<i>I was on an audition.</i>

1875
01:23:21,592 --> 01:23:23,594
<i>Because the Grizzlies fired me.</i>

1876
01:23:24,795 --> 01:23:26,331
<i>What?</i>

1877
01:23:27,798 --> 01:23:29,004
<i>Why didn't you tell us?</i>

1878
01:23:29,199 --> 01:23:30,337
<i>Because it's humiliating.</i>

1879
01:23:30,534 --> 01:23:32,036
<i>Why would they do that?</i>

1880
01:23:32,236 --> 01:23:34,079
<i>You're so good at that job.</i>

1881
01:23:34,938 --> 01:23:35,916
<i>Maybe not good enough.</i>

1882
01:23:38,475 --> 01:23:39,852
<i>Alice...</i>

1883
01:23:40,811 --> 01:23:41,789
<i>your mom was really hoping...</i>

1884
01:23:41,979 --> 01:23:45,392
<i>that this trip would help bring
her closer to her grandchildren.</i>

1885
01:23:46,216 --> 01:23:47,923
<i>And she and Harper have developed</i>

1886
01:23:48,018 --> 01:23:51,022
<i>a relationship that's kind of great...</i>

1887
01:23:51,288 --> 01:23:55,259
<i>and I don't want
to see that end just because I screwed up.</i>

1888
01:24:00,297 --> 01:24:01,833
<i>- What about you?
- Hmm?</i>

1889
01:24:02,266 --> 01:24:04,576
<i>Don't you want a relationship
with your grandchildren?</i>

1890
01:24:04,768 --> 01:24:06,475
<i>Of course I do.</i>

1891
01:24:06,670 --> 01:24:08,081
<i>I mean...</i>

1892
01:24:08,272 --> 01:24:12,152
<i>like an hour
before you came home, it was really good.</i>

1893
01:24:13,110 --> 01:24:15,215
<i>It's just that sometimes...</i>

1894
01:24:17,181 --> 01:24:18,888
<i>I don't feel...</i>

1895
01:24:19,283 --> 01:24:20,455
<i>What?</i>

1896
01:24:20,818 --> 01:24:24,493
<i>...welcome, here.</i>

1897
01:24:30,194 --> 01:24:32,299
<i>What happened to us, Dad?</i>

1898
01:24:36,100 --> 01:24:38,637
<i>How old were you when Harper was born?</i>

1899
01:24:38,869 --> 01:24:40,143
<i>- Twenty-six.
- Mmm-hmm.</i>

1900
01:24:40,337 --> 01:24:41,577
<i>Did you know what you were doing?</i>

1901
01:24:41,972 --> 01:24:42,973
<i>No.</i>

1902
01:24:43,941 --> 01:24:46,854
<i>I was 23 when you came along.</i>

1903
01:24:47,044 --> 01:24:50,685
<i>And I was terrified, because you didn't
come with any instructions.</i>

1904
01:24:50,881 --> 01:24:52,690
<i>And I thought I was doing okay.</i>

1905
01:24:52,883 --> 01:24:57,195
<i>Because unlike my father,
I wasn't constantly telling you...</i>

1906
01:24:57,387 --> 01:25:00,368
<i>what an annoying little waste
of time you were...</i>

1907
01:25:00,557 --> 01:25:02,628
<i>and believe me, I'm cleaning that up.</i>

1908
01:25:02,826 --> 01:25:05,636
<i>And I thought that we were
actually having fun.</i>

1909
01:25:05,829 --> 01:25:09,299
<i>Me and the weather girl...</i>

1910
01:25:09,500 --> 01:25:13,107
<i>and the cutest little girl you ever saw,
travelling around the country.</i>

1911
01:25:13,303 --> 01:25:16,182
<i>But then years go by,
and your daughter goes off to college...</i>

1912
01:25:16,373 --> 01:25:20,014
<i>and she doesn't come home
for Thanksgiving or Christmas.</i>

1913
01:25:21,078 --> 01:25:22,614
<i>Or summers.</i>

1914
01:25:22,813 --> 01:25:24,156
<i>Or ever.</i>

1915
01:25:24,848 --> 01:25:28,125
<i>And you get these clues, this inkling...</i>

1916
01:25:28,318 --> 01:25:31,424
<i>that perhaps all those years
she wasn't having such a good time...</i>

1917
01:25:31,622 --> 01:25:36,662
<i>and that maybe she thought
you didn't do such a good job.</i>

1918
01:25:36,860 --> 01:25:39,739
<i>And that really hurts. Doesn't it?</i>

1919
01:25:42,399 --> 01:25:44,072
<i>Yes.</i>

1920
01:25:44,434 --> 01:25:47,904
<i>So, little girl,
I have to give you three put-ups.</i>

1921
01:25:49,273 --> 01:25:50,251
<i>- No, Dad.
- Please.</i>

1922
01:25:50,440 --> 01:25:51,350
<i>It's okay.</i>

1923
01:25:51,542 --> 01:25:55,012
<i>Harper, Turner, Barker.</i>

1924
01:25:55,212 --> 01:25:57,692
<i>They're great kids
and you're a really good mother.</i>

1925
01:25:58,615 --> 01:25:59,616
<i>Yeah.</i>

1926
01:25:59,816 --> 01:26:02,558
<i>I'm basking in the glow
of my children's affection.</i>

1927
01:26:02,753 --> 01:26:04,858
<i>Harper? She didn't mean anything.</i>

1928
01:26:05,055 --> 01:26:06,363
<i>I mean, she's 12.</i>

1929
01:26:06,557 --> 01:26:08,559
<i>Get ready, it's going to get a lot worse.</i>

1930
01:26:09,793 --> 01:26:13,605
<i>Only, don't let her turn her back on you.</i>

1931
01:26:13,797 --> 01:26:15,743
<i>Because that will break your heart.</i>

1932
01:26:18,769 --> 01:26:19,941
<i>Harper?</i>

1933
01:26:21,772 --> 01:26:22,750
<i>No. Um...</i>

1934
01:26:23,774 --> 01:26:28,052
<i>Barker has a special request
for tomorrow, before the audition.</i>

1935
01:26:28,645 --> 01:26:30,716
<i>And it involves all of us.</i>

1936
01:26:47,231 --> 01:26:50,940
<i>Carl, your two favourite things were milk
and tofu dogs.</i>

1937
01:26:51,134 --> 01:26:53,614
<i>Now, you can have both forever.</i>

1938
01:27:11,154 --> 01:27:13,725
<i>Grandma, thanks for decorating the box.</i>

1939
01:27:13,991 --> 01:27:16,995
<i>Oh, honey, it was my pleasure.</i>

1940
01:27:20,030 --> 01:27:21,839
<i>Um,Carl...</i>

1941
01:27:22,032 --> 01:27:24,512
<i>Can Artie say something nice for Carl?</i>

1942
01:27:24,701 --> 01:27:25,873
<i>Me?</i>

1943
01:27:35,512 --> 01:27:36,490
<i>How do you--.</i>

1944
01:27:38,015 --> 01:27:41,087
<i>I'm sorry, Carl.</i>

1945
01:27:41,285 --> 01:27:43,891
<i>He died so young.</i>

1946
01:27:44,621 --> 01:27:45,759
<i>Mmm.</i>

1947
01:27:45,956 --> 01:27:49,233
<i>How do you say goodbye
to somebody you could never say hello to?</i>

1948
01:27:49,426 --> 01:27:50,666
<i>It's hard.</i>

1949
01:27:51,962 --> 01:27:53,566
<i>I didn't get to see Carl very often,</i>

1950
01:27:53,664 --> 01:27:55,234
<i>but then again, nobody else did.</i>

1951
01:27:56,900 --> 01:27:59,380
<i>Except for Barker...</i>

1952
01:27:59,569 --> 01:28:02,345
<i>which is what made him so special.</i>

1953
01:28:03,307 --> 01:28:07,619
<i>Carl wasn't just Barker's friend,
he was a part of him.</i>

1954
01:28:07,811 --> 01:28:11,054
<i>And that made him a part of all of us.</i>

1955
01:28:13,550 --> 01:28:16,861
<i>Carl, you will forever be in our hearts.</i>

1956
01:28:17,554 --> 01:28:19,261
<i>Keep on hopping, buddy.</i>

1957
01:28:47,784 --> 01:28:48,592
<i>Okay.</i>

1958
01:28:48,785 --> 01:28:51,095
<i>Alice, you take Harper backstage.
We'll grab some seats.</i>

1959
01:28:51,288 --> 01:28:52,266
<i>Barker, Turner, you're with us.</i>

1960
01:28:52,489 --> 01:28:53,627
<i>- Good luck.
- Knock them dead.</i>

1961
01:28:53,824 --> 01:28:54,802
<i>Thanks.</i>

1962
01:28:54,991 --> 01:28:56,299
<i>Break a leg.</i>

1963
01:28:56,493 --> 01:28:57,904
<i>Bye, Dad.</i>

1964
01:29:20,283 --> 01:29:22,388
<i>Don't applaud. That's that woman!</i>

1965
01:29:23,153 --> 01:29:24,427
<i>Good evening.</i>

1966
01:29:24,654 --> 01:29:28,761
<i>Welcome family, friends
and distinguished judges...</i>

1967
01:29:28,959 --> 01:29:31,565
<i>to the Atlanta Performing Arts Centre.</i>

1968
01:29:31,762 --> 01:29:34,072
<i>I am Doctor Sch veer.</i>

1969
01:29:37,134 --> 01:29:40,980
<i>We have 74 amazingly talented musicians...</i>

1970
01:29:41,171 --> 01:29:45,642
<i>all vying for one position
at this prestigious conservatory.</i>

1971
01:29:45,842 --> 01:29:48,482
<i>So, without further ado I give you</i>

1972
01:29:48,578 --> 01:29:51,184
